/*Access modifiers:-
 * Public  :-If we call variable/method as public we will have the access across all the package
 * Private :-Variable/method is private we cannot access the out side the class
 * Protected :-If var/method is protected only child class which inherited the property of parent class can access the values in other packages [In same package we can access anywhere]
 * Default :- If user doesnot mentioned any modifiers then java will assign default access modifiers :--Here we can access method anywhere only in package   :- Outside the other package cannot allowed
 * -->It is applicable for variable also   :-- void m1()
 * 
 * 
 * If we want to access protected method outside the other package we can access it in child class only  which inherited the property of parent class
 * */